pan><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">: for >500,000 cells, use DNA\/RNA Universal AllPrep kit; for <500,000 cells, use Qiagen DNA\/RNA AllPrep Micro kit.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">a. Centrifuge cells, then carefully remove all supernatant by aspiration.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">b. Loosen pellet by flicking and add RLT Plus buffer (prepared with\u00a0\u00a0 Beta-mercaptoethanol)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>< 5\u00a0\u00a0x 10<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">6<\/span><span>cells, <\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span>5 x 10<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">6<\/span><span>\u2013 1 x 10<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">7<\/span><span>cells, <\/span><\/div><br\/><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">2.<\/span><span> Pipet the lysate directly into a QIAshredder spin column and centrifuge for 2 min at maximum speed.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">3.<\/span><span> Continue with AllPrep protocol, or snap freeze and store at <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  for future use.<\/div><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"8E8A11A0DE8211EBB6E59FB2DBD5964B","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":350,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"94AD1D20DE8211EBB6E59FB2DBD5964B","order_id":3,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":600,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"BC4008C0DE8211EBB6E59FB2DBD5964B","order_id":4,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":-80,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1208982,"guid":"CC788FA0DE8211EBB6E59FB2DBD5964B","previous_id":1208979,"previous_guid":"4E3A4B10DE8211EBB6E59FB2DBD5964B","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4BF9CECEC1BA42FB894244319F68054B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Links to kits used in post-processing"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F1C9312FB220425BA9522ED831AF5A5A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">1.<\/span><span> All recent samples (using 750pg input) were processed using Takara Pico kit with: <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com\/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.takarabio.com%2Flearning-centers%2Fnext-generation-sequencing%2Ftechnical-notes%2Frna-seq%2Fstranded-libraries-from-picogram-input-total-rna-(v2)&data=04%7C01%7Cliliang%40augusta.edu%7Cec7e1904692c40b7a9f708d95053662e%7C8783ac6bd05b4292b483e65f1fdfee91%7C0%7C0%7C637629141401911171%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&sdata=k042qCBvVFtDUJXPcxIJyhdop1Tbs6RpxQ5Zo6RauAU%3D&reserved=0\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">https:\/\/www.takarabio.com\/learning-centers\/next-generation-sequencing\/technical-notes\/rna-seq\/stranded-libraries-from-picogram-input-total-rna-(v2)<\/span><\/a><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">2.<\/span><span> All samples prior to 2020 (used 100ng input) were processed using Illumina TruSeq Stranded Total RNA Library prep Gold: <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.illumina.com\/products\/by-type\/sequencing-kits\/library-prep-kits\/truseq-stranded-total-rna.html\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">https:\/\/www.illumina.com\/products\/by-type\/sequencing-kits\/library-prep-kits\/truseq-stranded-total-rna.html<\/span><\/a><\/div><br\/><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"5D56DF5D3F11432887D5B4A9B2E6F054","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Note:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;\">The cells go through the All Prep kit to get RNA and then utilized for bulk RNA-seq processing.\u00a0From this preparation, we also acquire DNA which is used for Whole Genome Bisulphide Sequencing (WGBS).<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;\"><\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":"","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Bulk RNA sequencing (RNA-seq) is a quantitative method used to interrogate the transcriptome of a biological sample at a given point in time. This protocol describes a method for generating bulk RNA-seq libraries from human islet material. This method also allows for isolation of genomic DNA, which can be used for additional assays such as whole genome bisulphite sequencing.<\/span><\/div><br\/><br\/><br\/><\/div>","changed_on":1628779970}